"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. My whole goal is to try to create a world where we divert our organic waste back to the fields, back to organic soil, and that we create a recycling system for our organic matter. And this would fix most of our problems, I think, as an unsustainable culture. It would fix our waste problems. Of course, we'll have to deal with plastics and decay resistant substances at some point. But it would take care of a lot of our ecological problems. It would fix broken water cycles in large scale. If we could ever possibly do it at large scale, it would fix a lot of our health problems because eating foods grown out of fertile rich soil would actually kind of solve a lot of our autoimmune disorders, in my opinion, because it would fix our gut biomes. And I think that you know doing it at my garden is a great thing, but I want to kind of like try to also do it at scale. And so I have a business on farm compost where I'm trying to divert organic waste to farms where they can be sheet composted. Now, this is uh my project is uh in Needville with Messina Regenerative and my good buddy Riley, who runs that farm, and behind me you'll see the blue 55 gallon food grade barrels that I transport this waste to in. And uh you can see the picture here of the the trailer all loaded up in Neadville, and I drop those off uh two times a month. Uh, generally it's about six, seven, eight, ten barrels from me, two or three better uh barrels from uh federal grill, and then uh sometimes we also have some from cranky carrot, but I'm not the one who picks those up. And all of this is going towards sheet composting, it's towards large-scale composting. But of course, I'm a one-man show right now. The business is just taking off. I would need funding, I would need trucks, I would need drivers, I would need accounts, and at the end of the day, the whole business is centered around getting paid to carry away people's waste because that is the model and that is how the whole thing can get propelled forward as an external revenue source on top of the fertile soil. Anyway, I think if I can get this going, uh, that could really go a long way. I'm starting at some baby steps. The first thing I'm doing is working on my own garden in my own life, composting there. And I do about one barrel every two weeks. And soon I'm gonna do a video showing how I do a make a barrel into compost out in my backyard. But I'd like to fill up a bunch more of these. I'd like to get this business developed and going. I it's just a matter of finding time for it and committing to it. Anyway, thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.88,\n      \"end\": 2.4,\n      \"duration\": 1.52,\n      \"confidence\": 0.98,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.88,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.995\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.2,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 1.36,\n          \"end\": 1.6,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.6,\n          \"end\": 1.92,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.92,\n          \"end\": 2.08,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \".\",\n          \"start\": 2.08,\n          \"end\": 2.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.893\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \" My whole goal is to try to create a world where we divert our organic waste back to the fields, back to organic soil, and that we create 